  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The proud have hid a snare for me - Haughty; arrogant; oppressive men. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 35:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", note; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 57:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", note.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And cords - Strings; twine; as those do who lay a net to catch birds, and who design to spring it upon them unawares.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They have spread a net by the wayside - Where I may be expected to walk, and where it may be suddenly sprung upon me.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They have set gins for me - Snares, toils - such as are set for wild beasts. The meaning is, that they had not only made open war upon him, but they had sought to bring him into an ambush - to rush upon him suddenly when he was not on his guard, and did not know that, danger was near. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "They have set gins for me - Snares, toils - such as are set for wild beasts. The meaning is, that they had not only made open war upon him, but they had sought to bring him into an ambush - to rush upon him suddenly when he was not on his guard, and did not know that, danger was near. ",
            "children": []
