        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 58:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and the step that is made by the foot (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 85:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 119:133",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and here the two senses are undistinguishable. They are called גּאים on account of the inordinate ambition that infatuates them. The metaphors taken from the life of the hunter (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 141:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 142:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") are here brought together as it were into a body of synonyms. The meaning of ליד־מעגּל becomes explicable from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 142:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ליד, at hand, is equivalent to \"immediately beside\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 18:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 11:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Close by the path along which he has to pass, lie gins ready to spring together and ensnare him when he appears. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
